    <h3>Settings</h3>
    <p>Now the product has been activated and is rendered in the 3D globe.</p>
    <p>The availability of the product is additionally displayed in the bottom time-line as well as the currently selected time interval. You can create a new time interval selection by clicking and dragging on the time-line. The current time selection (grey area) can also be modified by clicking and dragging it or extending the (left and right) edges.</p>
    <p>It is possible to zoom in and out using the mouse wheel over the time-line as well as panning by clicking and dragging on the bottom of the time-line.</p>
    <p>Additionally we opened the product settings window (on the right). Product settings can be accessed by clicking on the <i class="fa fa-sliders"/>-symbol of a product.</p>
    <p>At any point you can use the "Save as Image" button of the 3D Globe (top right) to save the current visualisation.</p>
</section>
